models.description_html: So from wood working to laser craft, i have taken an old wood working design and made it a file for my laser. The cover plates will need to be duplicated to thicken the overall piece
models.edu_details:
Overview and Background

From the book "Making Working Wooden Locks" written by Tim Detweiler. I have built this design in wood on a scroll saw and out of steel in my forge. Figured making one out of acrylic would be cool

Lesson Plan and Activity

A good way to learn about locks and engineering them.

Materials Needed

I used a K40 Laser for my build. Used 3mm plywood for first trial run.
